      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted RH index within 15% of experimentally measured RH across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Maximum discrepancy across the five nominal validation points is 10%. All predictions satisfy the 15% acceptance criterion. Comparison performed exclusively on nominal-hardware experimental data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) directly linked to clinical endpoint; secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) support mechanistic interpretation.",
      "rationale": "RH index is the regulatory-accepted hemolysis metric for CPB devices. Shear stress and residence time distributions extracted and reviewed. QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision under nominal operating assumptions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities cover the same pump geometry, fluid properties, and operating range as the COU. Physical hardware fault modes are addressed per separate fault-tolerance documentation.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under CPB-representative conditions. The five operating points span the COU envelope. Physical fault modes such as bearing wear, seal degradation, and motor driver transients that may arise during in vivo extended perfusion are acknowledged as relevant to the operational context; however, these are stated to be covered by fault-tolerance documentation maintained elsewhere. No fault-state validation activities were conducted within this campaign."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
