      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection and hemolysis damage accumulation model justified by published literature and sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published rotating machinery validation studies. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) applied with sensitivity analysis on model constants. Model form uncertainty quantified and within acceptable bounds for MRL 2. All model form assessments assume nominal pump geometry and hardware state."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Inlet boundary conditions, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, and pump geometry inputs traceable to measurements with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs derived from nominal design drawings and controlled laboratory measurements. Input uncertainty propagated through Latin hypercube sampling (n=50). No degraded or fault-state input conditions (e.g., worn clearances, reduced bearing stiffness, fluctuating motor speed due to driver transients) are represented in the input uncertainty characterization."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
